#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:1
msgid "Updating Third Party Projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:3
msgid ""
"When updating a third party project, any changes to the imported project "
"itself (e.g., the `zlib/vtkzlib` directory for zlib), should go through the "
"`update.sh` framework. This framework ensures that all patches to the third "
"party projects are tracked externally and available for (preferably) "
"upstream or other projects also embedding the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:9
msgid ""
"The [](thirdparty-projects.md) document lists all projects grouped by import "
"method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:11
msgid "`update.sh` framework"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:12
msgid "`git submodule`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:13
msgid "`copy`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:16
msgid ""
"Any updates to projects imported through the `copy` method should first be "
"converted over to the `update.sh` framework."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:20
msgid "Updating a Project Upstream"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:22
msgid ""
"Ideally, any code changes to third party code should first be submitted to "
"the upstream project using whatever workflow they prefer or require.  Once "
"that is done, the changes can next be brought into VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:26
msgid "Updating the Import"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:28
msgid ""
"Examine the project's `update.sh` script and note the value of the `repo=` "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:30
msgid ""
"If it's referring to anything other than [Kitware's GitLab](https://gitlab."
"kitware.com/third-party), then skip to the next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:33
msgid ""
"Otherwise, you first need to bring in the upstream changes into the `third-"
"party` repo. To do that, first fork and clone the repository named in the "
"`repo=` field. Then use git commands to bring in a copy of the upstream "
"changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:37
msgid ""
"Here's an example of updating the `twisted` project from tag 17.1.0 to "
"17.5.0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:39
msgid ""
"$ cd twisted/\n"
"$ git checkout for/vtk\n"
"$ git fetch origin\n"
"$ git rebase --onto twisted-17.5.0 twisted-17.1.0\n"
"$ git push\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:47
msgid ""
"When deciding what to rebase, you should generally use the first commit in "
"the current history that isn't upstream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:50
msgid "Updating a Project into VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:52
msgid ""
"Bringing changes into VTK involves first deciding what to bring in. That is "
"specified in the `update.sh` script under the `tag=` field. Usually this is "
"a `for/vtk` branch, but may be `master`, or a tag, or any other Git "
"reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:56
msgid ""
"If `update.sh` needs to be edited (the usual case), create a branch in the "
"usual way and commit just those changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:59
msgid ""
"Next, run the `update.sh` script as below. This will update the local copy "
"of the project to the version specified within."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:62
msgid ""
"$ cd vtk/ThirdParty/zlib\n"
"$ git checkout -b update_zlib_YYYY_MM_DD\n"
"$ ./update.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:68
msgid ""
"Appending the date to the branch name is not necessary, it just prevents any "
"conflict in the event of you doing this procedure multiple times and "
"inadvertently using the same branch name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:71
msgid ""
"(All this requires a Git 2.5 or higher due the `worktree` tool being used to "
"simplify the availability of the commits to the main checkout.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:74
msgid ""
"Make sure to update the `SPDX_DOWNLOAD_LOCATION` in `CMakeLists.txt` to "
"reflect the changes made to the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:77
msgid ""
"Now you can review the change and make a merge request from the branch as "
"normal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:79
msgid "Porting a Project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:81
msgid ""
"When converting a project, if there are any local patches, a project should "
"be created [on Kitware's GitLab](https://gitlab.kitware.com/third-party) to "
"track it (requests may be filed on the [repo-requests][] repository). If the "
"upstream project does not use Git, it should be imported into Git (there may "
"be existing conversions available on Github already). The project's "
"description should indicate where the source repository lives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:88
msgid ""
"Once a mirror of the project is created, a branch named `for/foo` should be "
"created where patches for the `foo` project will be applied (i.e., `for/vtk` "
"for VTK's patches to the project). Usually, changes to the build system, the "
"source code for mangling, the addition of `.gitattributes` files, and other "
"changes belong here. Functional changes should be submitted upstream (but "
"may still be tracked so that they may be used)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:95
msgid "For mangling documentation, [some guidelines][] are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:100
msgid ""
"The basic steps to import a project `twisted` based on the tag "
"`twisted-17.1.0` looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:103
msgid ""
"$ git clone https://github.com/twisted/twisted.git\n"
"$ cd twisted/\n"
"$ git remote add kitware git@gitlab.kitware.com:third-party/twisted.git\n"
"$ git push -u kitware\n"
"$ git push -u kitware --tags\n"
"$ git checkout twisted-17.1.0\n"
"$ git checkout -b for/vtk\n"
"$ git push --set-upstream kitware for/vtk\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:114
msgid ""
"Making the initial import involves filling out the project's `update.sh` "
"script in its directory. The [update-common.sh](path:../../../../ThirdParty/"
"update-common.sh) script describes what is necessary, but in a nutshell, it "
"is basically metadata such as the name of the project and where it goes in "
"the importing project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:119
msgid ""
"The most important bit is the `extract_source` function which should subset "
"the repository. If all that needs to be done is to extract the files given "
"in the `paths` variable (described in the `update-common.sh` script), the "
"`git_archive` function may be used if the `git archive` tool generates a "
"suitable subset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:125
msgid "Make sure `update.sh` is executable before commit. On Unix, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:127
msgid "  $ chmod u+x update.sh && git add -u update.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:131
msgid "On Windows, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:133
msgid "  $ git update-index --chmod=+x update.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:137
msgid ""
"Also add an entry to [](thirdparty-projects.md) for the project, and "
"`CMakeLists.txt` and `module.cmake` as appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:140
msgid "Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:142
msgid ""
"The basic process involves a second branch where the third party project's "
"changes are tracked. This branch has a commit for each time it has been "
"updated and is stripped to only contain the relevant parts (no unit tests, "
"documentation, etc.). This branch is then merged into the main branch as a "
"subdirectory using the `subtree` merge strategy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/thirdparty.md:148
msgid ""
"Initial conversions will require a manual push by the maintainers since the "
"conversion involves a root commit which is not allowed under normal "
"circumstances. Please post a message on the [VTK Discourse][] forum asking "
"for assistance if necessary."
msgstr ""
